orig=The crops such as wheat oats and barly are looking well so far, as I mentioned before there has been very little sown in the settlement this season on account of the farmers being afraid of the grasshoppers. But on examining the ground where the eggs had been deposited in different parts of the settlement it was found that a little worm something like a maggot has been destroying all the eggs. So effectual has their work been that there has not a young grasshopper made its appearance yet. So upon the whole we hope to have a little crop in the Settlement yet and will be enabled to avoid the calamity that befell us two years ago. mno|Local time: mean|QC flag: missing|Image File: Winnipeg_USSI-401_M1958_1870-05-01_CP.jpg

orig=The crops in this vicinity look remarkably well, we have been blessed with moderate rains and warm growing weather, and the consequence is that the crops look better in this country than they have done for many years. Reports reach here that the grasshoppers are doing a great deal of harm in northern Minnesota, but these reports as yet want confirmation. It is to be hoped that it is not true, but that a kind Providence will avert this calamity which fear now more than any thing else. mno|Local time: mean|QC flag: passed|Image File: Winnipeg_USSI-401_M1958_1872-06-01_CP.jpg
